<TITLE> Shopkeeper killed at Lalbagh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 05 (bdnews24.com)A shopkeeper was killed in his sleep early on Friday at Lalbagh in the city, police said. The body of Ruhul Amin, 18, was recovered at 6am from a shop, Amin Metal, of 209/4 Lalbagh lane. Amin and his co-workers Sujon and Hridoy went to sleep together after finishing work at around 1:30am, said sub-inspector of Lalbagh Police Station Riad Mahmud. Hridoy told police that Sujon had tried to kill him pressing a pillow against his mouth at around 4am. At one point of scuffle Hridoy opened the shutter of the shop and fled. He did not find Sujon when he came back after sometime but saw Amin lying dead,. Police are quizzing Hridoy and trying to arrest Sujon, Mahmud said. bdne
